,
or
66
cents
,
in
the
fourth
quarter
ended
Aug.
31
,
up
from
$
58.2
million
,
or
59
cents
,
a
year
earlier
.
###
Analysts
say
the
handful
of
hospital
companies
that
are
still
publicly
traded
are
benefiting
from
several
trends
.
###
Most
important
,
hospital
admission
rates
are
stabilizing
after
several
years
of
decline
.
###
Moreover
,
companies
have
sold
off
many
of
their
smaller
,
less-profitable
hospitals
and
have
completed
painful
restructurings
.
###
Humana
's
