Thomas
Gorman
decribed
the
plan
as
one
step
toward
an
overall
settlement
of
the
W.
Herbert
Hunt
case
but
Hugh
Ray
,
attorney
for
Manufacturers
Hanover
,
called
it
``
silly
''
and
said
he
would
fight
it
